        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8"><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often do fire extinguishers need to be inspected in Garland, TX?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">In Garland, TX, fire extinguishers require monthly visual inspections (by building staff), annual professional inspections by a licensed technician, 6-year internal examinations, and 12-year hydrostatic testing per NFPA 10 and the International Fire Code (IFC).</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does a fire extinguisher inspection cost in Garland, TX?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Annual inspections in the DFW Metro (Garland) typically cost $15–$38 per unit. 6-year internal examinations run $25–$55 per unit. 12-year hydrostatic tests cost $30–$70 per unit. Volume discounts apply for properties with 20+ extinguishers.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who can inspect fire extinguishers in Garland, TX?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Monthly visual checks can be done by trained building staff. Annual, 6-year, and 12-year service must be performed by a licensed fire protection technician. Texas requires fire extinguisher service to be performed by a technician licensed through the Texas Department of Insurance (TDI) State Fire Marshal's Office. Verify your service provider holds a current Portable Fire Extinguisher license at tdi.texas.gov/fire.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What are the penalties for fire extinguisher violations in Garland?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The Garland Fire Department issues violation notices with correction periods for fire extinguisher deficiencies. Uncorrected violations carry escalating fines. Serious life-safety deficiencies face accelerated enforcement action.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Does Garland require fire extinguishers in all commercial buildings?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. The International Fire Code (IFC) requires portable fire extinguishers in all commercial, industrial, and multi-family residential buildings in Garland. Type, size, and placement depend on occupancy classification and hazard level per NFPA 10.</p></div></div>
